== Rice ==

In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a 
pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low 
simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Lime Crema ==

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1}(thinly sliced). 
Halve, core, and thinly slice @Long Green Pepper{1}(into strips).

In a small #bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon} and lime zest. Add water 
@water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season 
with @salt{} and @Pepper{}.

== Turkey and Fajita Veggies ==

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in large pan over medium-high heat. Add 
@Ground Turkey{10%ounce}, onion, green pepper, and @Mexican Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}. 
Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until veggies 
are browned and turkey is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @Tex-Mex Paste{1}, @water{1/4%cup}, and juice from two lime wedges 
(1/2 cup water and juice from four wedges for 4 servings); stir to combine.

> If turkey mixture seems too thick, add another splash of water.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{}. Top with turkey and fajita veggies. Sprinkle 
with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup} and drizzle with lime crema. Serve with 
remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.